description: When Wortham Industries mild-mannered employee, Thomas Marriot is called in to Mr. Wortham's office (dead since 3012), little does he know he's about to experience the adventure of a lifetime... literally! Get ready for THE PAST IS NOW!
name: The Past is Now!

description:
Things get real! The challenge is on, and Luiza seems to benefit from Radh˚'s special training

(did I mention Luiza had to keep training wwhile sleeping?). Anyway the fight isn't over, neither is the test.
name: No te muevas

description:
Avalon Two

Having worked out that they are not dealing with historical re-enactors, Williams and his troops look for a way out of this nightmare.

FINAL ISSUE! A bomb falls from the sky, threatening the good people of Gotham City, and Batman and the Green Hornet have just one chance to take out this deadly threat. Meanwhile, Franco Bollo, the man whose stolen stamps started General Gumm and The Joker's current crime spree, has himself been stolen. Will this enable the terrible twosome to fly away scot-free? Or will our heroes finally save the day?
name: The End of Crime's Tether

description:
The Transiberian Triple Threat!

It all comes down to this! A three way dance in the Siberian tundra for the title of World's Greatest! Bunyan boy, it's time to steppe up!
name: The Transiberian Triple Threat!

description: More people are turning up dead, and Harper might just be falling for the town's deputy, a handsome, rugged man whose wife died under mysterious circumstances...Based on acclaimed and NYT Bestselling author Charlaine Harris' hit Harper Connelly series, the first book of which is Grave Sight.
name: Chapter Four

description:
A Clockwork automaton falls into a brewery's fermentation tank, and gains sentience. Exactly the opposite of what would happen to a human being. He finds himself in a world sick to the core, searching for a miracle.

Could he be the answer? Is he ready for such responsibility? And why isn't anyone asking him what he wants?

The world has a vested interest in knowing how this anomaly came to be, but Ervin has other things on his mind, such as the freedom of his fellow Clockworks.
name: Tick Tock IPA 2

description:
Super Rangers

A Power Ranger parody issue! When a trip to the beach for spring break is interrupted by a giant monster, Stickboy transforms into Aqua Blue Ranger and teams up with Lavender Ranger (aka Psychoboy) to kick some butt. Robots, monsters, inexplicable scenery changes and unspeakable violence, what more could you ask for?
name: Super Rangers

description:
The mysterious island of Tartaruga begins to reveal its secrets as a new investigation begins for the Nekton Family.

Danger, secrets, peril, shocking revelations, and Ant doing something really stupid...

From James Tynion IV (writer of DC's TALON) and digital pioneer Jeremy Rock comes a new political horror thriller! There's something monstrous going on in Washington, D.C.--and the repercussions could affect the balance of world power!
name: Chapter Eight

description: Amber and Zavi finally come face to face with The Endling.

Back after much critical acclaim! It's the collected editions of Freestyle! The comic no-one thought would make it past the first issue! Created by Australian Mark Pursell who likes to think he can draw and write and stuff and occasionally can, Freestyle is a comic. It is funny and has words and pretty pictures!

Freestyle 04 - Tales Of Wrath

It's the start of a whole new trilogy! Chloe unleashes another of her crappy schemes! This time she is raising early designs of Stupid Cat from the grave and making them try and kill the current version of Stupid Cat, starting with Stupid Cat from 1995... What is the reason behind her scheme? It's bound to be something stupid and annoying but she must be stopped at all costs!

Freestyle 05 - Tales Of Envy

Chloe's idiotic scheme continues. This time Stupid Cat from 1997 is terrorising the current version of Stupid Cat and his gang. We also discover that Cactus has allergies to something he is in constant contact with and that mathematics can be deadly!

Freestyle 06 - Tales Of Gluten

Finally, the conclusion to this trilogy! In this issue Stupid Cat goes up against the previous version of himself. Fighting someone so close to yourself isn't as easy as it sounds and Current Stupid tries to reason with him. Unfortunately, Chloe and her Fake Cops will have none of that...

This issue also contains a special Super Butterflyman comic for the enjoyment of those who like butterflies that are super and ice cream.
name: Vol. 2

description: Can the Guardians of the Galaxy stop the War of Kings? When Black Bolt and Vulcan square off, and the Inhumans and Shi'ar ravage entire planets, the Guardians are stuck in the middle! As new discoveries are made and old friends are betrayed, the new Guardians must stand shoulder-to-shoulder with cosmic legends to survive! But when the Fault, a massive rift in reality, releases a viral xenoform that threatens to destroy the cosmos, the bruised and battered Guardians must return the creature to its own dimension before the unthinkable happens. Unfortunately, the Universal Church of Truth believes the creature is its savior and will stop at nothing to free the beast! But who is pulling the zealots' strings? Can the Guardians uncover the true threat and restore peace to a war-ravaged universe? Collecting GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY (2008) #13-25.
name: Volume 2

description:
What does it really take to be a Hero Cat? Find out as Ace leads Cassiopeia through some long-overdue training. Will she survive the journey from civilian to soldier?

Note: The digital edition (11/19/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Cassiopeia's Basic Training

description: In the recent uprisings against Superman, one of his allies has been conspicuously absent: the mystical being known as Raven. Find out what has become of her and what role Constantine has played in her absence.
name: Raven's Rescue; Ragman's Souls

volume.name: Injustice: Gods Among Us Year Three

description: Galahad investigates his mysterious "fan club"--with fatal results. Meanwhile, Nocturnus has solved a murder--but can he convince the police to follow his lead?

With this story arc's conclusion, "Johnny Saturn: Homeland Insecurity" part VI, everything changes for Joe, the fallen hero, but in ways no one would have expected! There is also the crazy action of John Underhall and Dr. Synn having tea on the veranda, and the ultimate, apocalyptic showdown of the Iron Brigade and the Squadron Premiere. Missiles will be fired, people will die for good, and an Age of Heroes will crumble to its end...

This edition of "Johnny Saturn" has 24 pages of comics, four characters' Who's Who pages, one Spire City map, and six bonus sketchbook pages, all for 38 total pages of content!
name: Homeland Insecurity VI

description: Revived and trying to exist as a rotting corpse, Aten Ra seeks the help of the wizard Ragmar and become embroiled in his battle with the evil sorceress Kshayla in the Tower of the Black Apes.

Sludgetime For Zombo

Pewfell is working two jobs. By day he is a wizard in the city sewer patrol, by night he is a collector of skin-flakes at Baron Samedi's rest-care home for the undead. Meanwhile his wife, Tina the Warrior Princess, is due to give birth to their first child at any moment and an army of chaos threatens to attack the city.
name: Sludgetime For Zombo

description:
When Queen Neva takes Yuri and Valentina prisoner, she puts them to work in the infamous Blood Mines of Woodmere. Meanwhile, Neva and her dark sorcerer Narog devise a plot to steal their power. Also, a steadfast messenger must carry the fate of the war across an unforgiving landscape!

Note: The digital edition (11/19/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Ever had a crappy job? Well, Poopert sure does! He's a poop working at Poop Office. Thrill at his adventures interacting with his officemates Fecelia, Alpoop, Buttany, his boss Mr. Poopson, and many more!

The fifth issue features more tales from the only office staffed entirely by poop! Find out what happens when Buttany and Fecelia try to fix the office clock! Learn why Poopert is wearing that eyepatch. And get ready for Poopert on vacation! Also learn Poopert's deepest fantasies!

Includes Poop Office 61-78, Shorts 52-54, and several deleted scenes!
Walker and Pilgrim are faced with the future of powers, and it ain't pretty.

A promise is a promise. Raider travels to Australia to deliver a dying man's message to his daughter. Simple enough, except for two things-Raider is the man's killer and the daughter is Agent Vega! Can Raider and Vega put aside their differences long enough to stop the lethal plan of a Dominator splinter group? Plus: Ben has to deal with the ghosts of his past.
name: Dead Men's Tales

description:
The Frigate Bird

Months following the birth of Peter and Ada's baby, Jonah is hard at work trying to build a new band with Peter. Meanwhile, Jonah's relationship with Sarah has grown sexually, but not much otherwise. Despite feeling compelled to be in one another's company, the two struggle painfully to get an understanding of both each other, and the new, toxic beast that their dubious, mutual attraction has created. Tempers flare and nerve-endings fray, as old behaviors and new attitudes threaten to crack Jonah's well-crafted veneer of quiet strength. Will... the lone wolf... survive?
name: The Frigate Bird

description: Teenage fugitives Nico, Gert, Karolina, Chase and Molly are survivors. After learning their parents were secretly super villains, the kids discovered special skills of their own and toppled their parents' criminal empire, the Pride. Now, the Runaways meet Victor Mancha, unknowing son of another infamous super villain, as a meddling ex-super-hero support group tries to force the Runaways off the streets! Meanwhile, one Runaway deals with an unexpected legacy, and the team helps Cloak and Dagger hunt a stalker - which leads to confrontations with the New Avengers and the X-Men, who have their own ideas about what's best for the Runaways. But all of this pales when the Pride returns - with an all-new lineup! Who are these shadowy new players, and what do they want with the Runaways?! Collecting RUNAWAYS (2005) #1-18 and FREE COMIC BOOK DAY 2006 (X-MEN/RUNAWAYS) #1.
name: Volume Two

description: Things go haywire when the science-villain who captured Diana brainwashes her! Mary Marvel and Supergirl are counting on Wonder Woman. . . can she defeat mind-control, androids AND the villain in time?
name: No Chains Can Hold Her! Part 2

description: Wonder Woman appears in a trio of tales with some offbeat guest stars! First, Diana and her friend Etta Candy are captured by Ra's al Ghul, but he's not the most surprising soul they meet. Then, a Thanagarian menace returns to Earth, and you won't believe what Diana must do in her battle with Byth! Plus, the conclusion to Gilbert Hernandez’s tale pitting Wonder Woman against a science villain, android minions AND brainwashing!
name: No Chains Can Hold Her!; Attack of the 500-Foot Wonder-Woman; Ghosts and Gods

description: When Starfire develops a massive crush on the latest teen pop sensation, Robin will stop at nothing to recapture her attention--even if he must become a teen idol himself!
name: Chapter Thirteen

description: The groundbreaking digital comic returns! Half a million downloads, and the inspiration for everything from Thrillbent itself to comics like Moth City! Read where it all began! Chris and Valentine return to Paris, and attempt to wake Nell from her comatose state. But as Valentine continues to press his love for Nell, he risks alienating the only people he knows in the world... if they don't betray him first!

Cutting Room

Cutting Room Floor

Ai is bootlegged to a new tape by the sympathetic old clerk of the Gokuraku Video Shop and is living in Yota's house. As Yota's romance with his first girlfriend, Nobuku, enters its final stages, Video Girl Mai is sent by Ai's creator to edit out Ai's very existence!
name: Cutting Room

description: The next chapter of Wolverine's life begins now, but it looks like it's going to be an extremely short and painful chapter! Stranded in Japan, stripped of his healing factor, Wolverine confronts his future - and it ain't a bright one. As Logan, Iron Fist and Shang-Chi take on an army of deadly ninja, Logan comes clean to his old friends - and Sabretooth marks Wolverine's new love Pinch for death, unless Wolverine and his S.H.I.E.L.D. cavalry can reach her in time. And when Sabretooth prepares to remake the world in his image, he forces Logan into a bloody final showdown. It's all led up to this as Wolverine enters his most dire hour - and possibly his final battle! It's the beginning of the end for Wolverine! The title says it all! Collecting WOLVERINE (2014) #8-12 and ANNUAL #1.
name: Book 2
